120void dna_plot::CreateSegmentationGraph(const plotGraphMode& graphMode)
121{
122
123 // Execute gnuplot in a separate process
124 InvokeGnuplot();
125
126 // clean up gnuplot command file and input data file
127 CleanupGnuplotFiles(graphMode);
128}
129
130void dna_plot::CleanupGnuplotFiles(const plotGraphMode& graphMode)
131{
132 if (pprj_->p._keep_gen_files)
133 return;
134
135 std::stringstream ss;
136 ss << _DELETE_CMD_;
137
138 // remove gnuplot command file
139 ss << pprj_->p._gnuplot_cmd_file << " ";
140
141 // remove gnuplot input file
142 switch (graphMode)
143 {
144 case StationsMode:
145 ss << seg_stn_graph_file_;
146 break;
147 case MeasurementsMode:
148 ss << seg_msr_graph_file_;
149 break;
150 default:
151 break;
152 }
153
154 // delete
155 std::string system_file_cmd = ss.str();
156 std::system(system_file_cmd.c_str());
157}
158
159void dna_plot::CreategnuplotGraphEnvironment(project_settings* pprj, const plotGraphMode& graphMode)
160{
161 InitialiseAppsandSystemCommands();
162
163 // Set up the environment
164 pprj_ = pprj;
165
166 if (!boost::filesystem::exists(pprj_->g.output_folder))
167 {
168 std::stringstream ss("CreategnuplotGraphEnvironment(): Output path does not exist... \n\n ");
169 ss << pprj_->g.output_folder << ".";
170 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, NULL);
171 }
172
173 output_folder_ = pprj_->g.output_folder;
174 network_name_ = pprj_->g.network_name;
175
177 // create gnuplot command file and set gnuplot parameters
178 std::string gnuplot_cmd_filename("graph_" + network_name_);
179
180 std::string gnuplot_pic_name;
181 switch (graphMode)
182 {
183 case StationsMode:
184 gnuplot_pic_name = (network_name_ + "_graph_stn");
185 gnuplot_cmd_filename.append("_stns");
186 break;
187 case MeasurementsMode:
188 gnuplot_pic_name = (network_name_ + "_graph_msr");
189 gnuplot_cmd_filename.append("_msrs");
190 break;
191 }
192
193 gnuplot_cmd_filename.append(_CMD_EXT_);
194 std::string gnuplot_cmd_file(output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + gnuplot_cmd_filename);
195
196 pprj_->p._gnuplot_cmd_file = gnuplot_cmd_file;
197
198 // create pdf filename
199 pprj_->p._pdf_file_name = output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + gnuplot_pic_name + ".pdf";
200
201 switch (graphMode)
202 {
203 case StationsMode:
204 PlotGnuplotDatFileStns();
205 break;
206 case MeasurementsMode:
207 PlotGnuplotDatFileMsrs();
208 break;
209 }
210
211 PrintGnuplotCommandFile(gnuplot_cmd_file, graphMode);
212
213}
214
215void dna_plot::InvokeGnuplot()
216{
217 // Invoke gnuplot using absolute path
218 std::string system_file_cmd = "gnuplot " + boost::filesystem::absolute(pprj_->p._gnuplot_cmd_file).string();
219
220 // set up a thread group to execute the gnuplot in parallel
221 boost::thread gnuplot_thread{dna_create_threaded_process(system_file_cmd)};
222
223 // go!
224 gnuplot_thread.join();
225}

230void dna_plot::PlotGnuplotDatFileStns()
231{
232 seg_stn_graph_file_ = output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + network_name_ + "-stn.seg.data";
233
234 std::ofstream seg_data;
235 try {
236 // Create gnuplot station segment data file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
237 file_opener(seg_data, seg_stn_graph_file_);
238 }
239 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
240 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
241 }
242
243 std::stringstream ss(""), st("");
244 ss << "\"Max block size (" << std::setprecision(0) << blockThreshold_ << ")\" ";
245 st << "\"Min inner stns (" << minInnerStns_ << ")\" ";
246 seg_data << std::setw(HEADER_18) << std::left << "Block" <<
247 std::setw(HEADER_32) << std::left << ss.str() <<
248 std::setw(HEADER_32) << std::left << st.str() <<
249 std::setw(HEADER_25) << std::left << "\"Total block size\"" <<
250 std::setw(HEADER_18) << std::left << "\"Inner stns\"" <<
251 std::setw(HEADER_18) << std::left << "\"Junction stns\"" << std::endl;
252
253 for (UINT32 block=0; block<blockCount_; ++block)
254 seg_data << std::setw(HEADER_18) << std::left << block+1 <<
255 std::setw(HEADER_32) << std::left << std::setprecision(0) << blockThreshold_ << // threshold
256 std::setw(HEADER_32) << std::left << std::setprecision(0) << minInnerStns_ << // threshold
257 std::setw(HEADER_25) << std::left << v_ISL_.at(block).size() + v_JSL_.at(block).size() << // block size
258 std::setw(HEADER_18) << std::left << v_ISL_.at(block).size() << // inner station count
259 std::setw(HEADER_18) << std::left << v_JSL_.at(block).size() << std::endl; // junction station count
260
261 seg_data.close();
262}

265void dna_plot::PlotGnuplotDatFileMsrs()
266{
267 seg_msr_graph_file_ = output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + network_name_ + "-msr.seg.data";
268
269 std::ofstream seg_data;
270 try {
271 // Create gnuplot measurement segment data file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
272 file_opener(seg_data, seg_msr_graph_file_);
273 }
274 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
275 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
276 }
277
278 UINT16 c;
279
280 // print header
281 seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << "Block";
282 std::stringstream ss;
283 ss << "\"Total measurements\"";
284 seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << ss.str();
285
286 for (c=0; c<_combined_msr_list.size(); c++)
287 {
288 if (parsemsrTally_.MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) == 0)
289 continue;
290 ss.str("");
291 ss << "\"" << measurement_name<char, std::string>(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) << " (" <<
292 parsemsrTally_.MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) << ")\"";
293 seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << ss.str();
294 }
295 seg_data << std::endl;
296
297 // Tally up measurement types for each block
298 ComputeMeasurementCount();
299
300 // print measurement tally for each block
301 UINT32 block;
302 for (block=0; block<blockCount_; ++block)
303 {
304 seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << block + 1;
305 seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << v_msr_tally_.at(block).TotalCount();
306
307 for (c=0; c<_combined_msr_list.size(); c++)
308 {
309 // do any measurements of this type exist at all?
310 if (parsemsrTally_.MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) > 0)
311 {
312 // yes, so test if this block has such measurements...
313 //if (v_msr_tally_.at(block).MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) == 0) // no
314 // seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << "-";
315 //else
316 seg_data << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << std::left << v_msr_tally_.at(block).MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c));
317 }
318 }
319 seg_data << std::endl;
320 }
321
322 seg_data.close();
323}

325
326void dna_plot::ComputeMeasurementCount()
327{
328 v_msr_tally_.resize(blockCount_);
329
330 UINT32 block;
331 it_vUINT32 _it_msr;
332
333 for (block=0; block<blockCount_; ++block)
334 {
335 for (_it_msr=v_CML_.at(block).begin(); _it_msr<v_CML_.at(block).end(); _it_msr++)
336 {
337 // Increment single station measurement counters...
338 switch (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).measType)
339 {
340 case 'A': // Horizontal angle
341 v_msr_tally_.at(block).A++;
342 break;
343 case 'B': // Geodetic azimuth
344 v_msr_tally_.at(block).B++;
345 break;
346 case 'C': // Chord dist
347 v_msr_tally_.at(block).C++;
348 break;
349 case 'D': // Direction set
350 if (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).measStart == xMeas)
351 v_msr_tally_.at(block).D += bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount1;
352 break;
353 case 'E': // Ellipsoid arc
354 v_msr_tally_.at(block).E++;
355 break;
356 case 'G': // GPS Baseline (treat as single-baseline cluster)
357 v_msr_tally_.at(block).G ++;
358 break;
359 case 'X': // GPS Baseline cluster
360 if (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).measStart == xMeas)
361 {
362 if (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount1 == bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount2 + 1)
363 v_msr_tally_.at(block).X += (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount1 * 3);
364 }
365 break;
366 case 'H': // Orthometric height
367 v_msr_tally_.at(block).H++;
368 break;
369 case 'I': // Astronomic latitude
370 v_msr_tally_.at(block).I++;
371 break;
372 case 'J': // Astronomic longitude
373 v_msr_tally_.at(block).J++;
374 break;
375 case 'K': // Astronomic azimuth
376 v_msr_tally_.at(block).K++;
377 break;
378 case 'L': // Level difference
379 v_msr_tally_.at(block).L++;
380 break;
381 case 'M': // MSL arc
382 v_msr_tally_.at(block).M++;
383 break;
384 case 'P': // Geodetic latitude
385 v_msr_tally_.at(block).P++;
386 break;
387 case 'Q': // Geodetic longitude
388 v_msr_tally_.at(block).Q++;
389 break;
390 case 'R': // Ellipsoidal height
391 v_msr_tally_.at(block).R++;
392 break;
393 case 'S': // Slope distance
394 v_msr_tally_.at(block).S++;
395 break;
396 case 'V': // Zenith distance
397 v_msr_tally_.at(block).V++;
398 break;
399 case 'Y': // GPS point cluster
400 if (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).measStart == xMeas)
401 {
402 if (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount1 == bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount2 + 1)
403 v_msr_tally_.at(block).Y += (bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).vectorCount1 * 3);
404 }
405 break;
406 case 'Z': // Vertical angle
407 v_msr_tally_.at(block).Z++;
408 break;
409 default:
410 std::stringstream ss;
411 ss << "ComputeMeasurementCount(): Unknown measurement type: " << bmsBinaryRecords_.at(*_it_msr).measType << std::endl;
412 throw NetPlotException(ss.str(), 0);
413 }
414 }
415 }
416}

419void dna_plot::PrintGnuplotCommandFile(const std::string& gnuplot_cmd_file, const plotGraphMode& graphMode)
420{
421 try {
422 // Create gnuplot batch file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
423 file_opener(gnuplotbat_file_, gnuplot_cmd_file);
424 }
425 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
426 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
427 }
428
429 //if (output_folder_ != ".")
430 // gnuplotbat_file_ << "cd '" << output_folder_ << "'" << std::endl << std::endl;
431
432 //gnuplotbat_file_ << "set terminal postscript eps enhanced color solid colortext" << std::endl << std::endl;
433 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set terminal pdf enhanced color solid linewidth 0.75" << std::endl << std::endl;
434 // gnuplot requires single quotes for filenames
435 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set output '" << pprj_->p._pdf_file_name << "'" << std::endl;
436
437 // histogram style
438 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set style fill transparent solid 0.4" << std::endl;
439 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set boxwidth 0.5" << std::endl;
440
441 UINT32 upperLimit(0), block(0);
442
443 switch (graphMode)
444 {
445 case StationsMode:
446 for (block=0; block<blockCount_; ++block)
447 if (upperLimit < (v_ISL_.at(block).size() + v_JSL_.at(block).size()))
448 upperLimit = static_cast<UINT32>(v_ISL_.at(block).size() + v_JSL_.at(block).size());
449
450 upperLimit = std::max(blockThreshold_, upperLimit);
451
452 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set title \"" << "Station segmentation summary for " << network_name_ << "\" font \"Calibri,16\" noenhanced" << std::endl << std::endl;
453 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set key outside center bottom horizontal Left reverse enhanced autotitles samplen 2.5 font \"Calibri,8\"" << std::endl;
454 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set key width -2 height 2.5" << std::endl << std::endl;
455
456 break;
457 case MeasurementsMode:
458 for (block=0; block<blockCount_; ++block)
459 if (upperLimit < v_msr_tally_.at(block).TotalCount())
460 upperLimit = v_msr_tally_.at(block).TotalCount();
461
462 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set title \"" << "Measurement segmentation summary for " << network_name_ << "\" font \"Calibri,20\" noenhanced" << std::endl << std::endl;
463 //gnuplotbat_file_ << "set key outside right top vertical Left reverse enhanced autotitles columnhead box samplen 2.5 font \"Calibri,8\"" << std::endl;
464 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set key outside center bottom horizontal Left reverse enhanced autotitles columnhead samplen 2.5 font \"Calibri,8\"" << std::endl;
465 //gnuplotbat_file_ << "set key width -15 height 0" << std::endl << std::endl;
466 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set key width -2 height 2.5" << std::endl << std::endl;
467
468 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set style histogram rowstacked title offset character 0, 0, 0" << std::endl;
469 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set style data histograms" << std::endl;
470 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set datafile missing '-'" << std::endl;
471 gnuplotbat_file_ << std::endl;
472 break;
473 }
474
475 upperLimit = upperLimit + upperLimit / 10;
476
477 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set format x '%.0f'" << std::endl;
478 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set format y '%.0f'" << std::endl;
479 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set yrange[0:" << upperLimit << "]" << std::endl;
480 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set auto x" << std::endl;
481 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set ytics scale 0.25 font \"Calibri,8\"" << std::endl;
482
483 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics scale 0.25 nomirror" << std::endl;
484
485 UINT32 fontSize(8);
486 if (blockCount_ > 5000)
487 {
488 fontSize = 5;
489 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics 0,500 font \"Calibri,6\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
490 }
491 else if (blockCount_ > 1000)
492 {
493 fontSize = 5;
494 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics 0,100 font \"Calibri,6\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
495 }
496 else if (blockCount_ > 500)
497 {
498 fontSize = 5;
499 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics 0,50 font \"Calibri,5\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
500 }
501 else if (blockCount_ > 100)
502 {
503 fontSize = 5;
504 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics 0,10 font \"Calibri,6\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
505 }
506 else if (blockCount_ > 50)
507 {
508 fontSize = 6;
509 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics 0,5 font \"Calibri,8\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
510 }
511 else
512 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xtics 0,1 font \"Calibri,8\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
513
514
515 // x-axis label
516 std::stringstream ss("");
517 ss << "Segmented Network Blocks (Total " << std::fixed << std::setprecision(0) << blockCount_ << ")";
518 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set xlabel '" << ss.str() << "' font \"Calibri,10\"" << std::endl;
519
520 switch (graphMode)
521 {
522 case StationsMode:
523 PrintGnuplotCommandFileStns(fontSize);
524 break;
525 case MeasurementsMode:
526 PrintGnuplotCommandFileMsrs(fontSize);
527 break;
528 }
529
530 gnuplotbat_file_.close();
531}

560
561void dna_plot::PrintGnuplotCommandFileMsrs(const UINT32& fontSize)
562{
563 std::stringstream ss("");
564 ss << "Measurement Count (Total " << std::fixed << std::setprecision(0) << measurementCount_ << ")";
565 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set ylabel '" << ss.str() << "' font \"Calibri,10\"" << std::endl << std::endl;
566
567 // All colours based on a palette:
568 // https://coolors.co/ffd275-235789-da5552-43aa8b-39a9db
569
570 UINT32 line(1);
571 ss.str("");
572 ss << "\"#4169e1\"";
573 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set style line " << line++ << " lw 1 lt 1 pt 7 ps 0.5 lc rgb " << std::left << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << ss.str() << " # total block size" << std::endl; // royalblue
574
575 // print measurements for each block
576 UINT32 c;
577 std::string colour;
578 it_pair_string _it_colour;
579
580 std::sort(pprj_->p._msr_colours.begin(), pprj_->p._msr_colours.end(), ComparePairFirst<std::string>());
581
582 for (c=0; c<_combined_msr_list.size(); c++)
583 {
584 if (parsemsrTally_.MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) < 1)
585 continue;
586 colour = _combined_msr_list.at(c);
587 _it_colour = equal_range(pprj_->p._msr_colours.begin(), pprj_->p._msr_colours.end(),
588 colour, ComparePairFirst<std::string>());
589
590 if (_it_colour.first == _it_colour.second)
591 colour = "light-gray";
592 else
593 colour = _it_colour.first->second;
594
595 ss.str("");
596 ss << "\"" << colour << "\"";
597 gnuplotbat_file_ << "set style line " << line++ << " lw 1 lt 1 pt 7 ps 0.5 lc rgb " << std::left << std::setw(PRINT_VAR_PAD) << ss.str() <<
598 " # \"" << measurement_name<char, std::string>(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) << "\"" << std::endl;
599
600 }
601 gnuplotbat_file_ << std::endl;
602
603 //UINT32 block(0);
604 //if (v_msr_tally_.at(block).MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) == 0)
605 // continue;
606
607 // plot total measurement count
608 line = 3;
609 UINT32 linestyle(line-1), msrs(0);
610 gnuplotbat_file_ << "plot '";
611 measurementCategories_ = 0;
612
613 for (c=0; c<_combined_msr_list.size(); c++)
614 {
615 if (parsemsrTally_.MeasurementCount(_combined_msr_list.at(c)) < 1)
616 continue;
617 if (msrs++ > 0)
618 gnuplotbat_file_ << ", \\" << std::endl << " '";
619 gnuplotbat_file_ << seg_msr_graph_file_ << "' using " << line++ << ":xtic(1) ls " << linestyle++;
620 measurementCategories_++;
621 }
622
623 gnuplotbat_file_ << ", \\" << std::endl << " '" << seg_msr_graph_file_ <<
624 "' using 0:2:(sprintf(\"%d\",$2)) with labels font \"Calibri," <<
625 fontSize << "\" center offset 0,0.5 notitle" << std::endl;
626
627}

682
683void dna_plot::FinaliseGMTParameters()
684{
685 //
686 // At this point, all limit values are in decimal degrees
687 //
688
689 if (rightDeg_ < leftDeg_)
690 {
691 std::stringstream ss;
692 ss << "Right limit cannot be less than left limit." << std::endl;
693 throw NetPlotException(ss.str(), 0);
694 }
695
696 if (upperDeg_ < lowerDeg_)
697 {
698 std::stringstream ss;
699 ss << "Upper limit cannot be less than lower limit." << std::endl;
700 throw NetPlotException(ss.str(), 0);
701 }
702
703 // calculate dimensions of data extents
704 dWidth_ = (rightDeg_ - leftDeg_);
705 dHeight_ = (upperDeg_ - lowerDeg_);
706
707 // if data is a single point (or a very small area)
708 if (dHeight_ < 0.00005)
709 dHeight_ += seconds15;
710 if (dWidth_ < 0.00005)
711 dWidth_ += seconds15;
712
713 // capture smallest dimension
714 dDimension_ = (std::min(dWidth_, dHeight_));
715
716 // Determine a buffer to envelope the entire plot, set to
717 // 10% of the width/height (whichever is smaller)
718 dBuffer_ = (dDimension_ * (0.1));
719
720 // calculate latitude at which to place the scale bar
721 dScaleLat_ = (lowerDeg_ - dBuffer_ / 2.0);
722
723 // calculate centre point of data
724 centre_width_ = (rightDeg_ + leftDeg_) / 2.0;
725 centre_height_ = (upperDeg_ + lowerDeg_) / 2.0;
726
727 // Has the user specified certain limits, or will the data be used to
728 // define the limits
729 if (default_limits_)
730 {
731 // OK, the spatial extent of the data sets the limits, so
732 // add a buffer accordingly
733 upperDeg_ += dBuffer_;
734 lowerDeg_ -= dBuffer_;
735 leftDeg_ -= dBuffer_;
736 rightDeg_ += dBuffer_;
737
738 if (dDimension_ > seconds60)
739 {
740 // round down to nearest 5"
741 leftDeg_ = leftDeg_ - fmod(leftDeg_, seconds05);
742 lowerDeg_ = lowerDeg_ - fmod(lowerDeg_, seconds05);
743 rightDeg_ = rightDeg_ + (seconds05 - fmod(rightDeg_, seconds05));
744 upperDeg_ = upperDeg_ + (seconds05 - fmod(upperDeg_, seconds05));
745 }
746 }
747 else
748 {
749 // Limits have been calculated via user input, so simply calculate
750 // calculate latitude at which the scale bar
751 // will be placed
752 centre_width_ = pprj_->p._plot_centre_longitude;
753 centre_height_ = pprj_->p._plot_centre_latitude;
754
755 dScaleLat_ = lowerDeg_ + dBuffer_ / 2.0;
756 }
757
758 // prevent limit values from exceeding 'normal' limits
759 if (default_limits_)
760 {
761 if (lowerDeg_ < -90.)
762 lowerDeg_ = -90.;
763 if (lowerDeg_ > 90.)
764 lowerDeg_ = 90.;
765 }
766
767 // set the position of the error ellipse legend
768 uncertainty_legend_long_ = leftDeg_ + dBuffer_;
769 uncertainty_legend_lat_ = dScaleLat_;
770
771 if (pprj_->p._plot_correction_arrows)
772 {
773 // set the position of the correction arrow legend
774 // put the corrections legend on the right hand side
775 arrow_legend_long_ = rightDeg_ - dBuffer_ * 2.0;
776 arrow_legend_lat_ = dScaleLat_;
777 }
778
779 switch (pprj_->p._projection)
780 {
781 case world:
782 case orthographic:
783 case robinson:
784 default_paper_width_ = 27.7;
785 default_paper_height_ = 20.1;
786 break;
787 default:
788 default_paper_width_ = 59.4;
789 default_paper_height_ = 42.0;
790 }
791
792 // Portrait or Landscape?
793 // A3 paper width (landscape) is 42cm, and (portrait) is 29.7cm. Less
794 // nomenclature (~2 cm), this leaves an available width for plotting
795 // of 40cm L or 27.7cm P
796 //
797 title_block_height_ = 6;
798 page_width_ = default_paper_width_; // centimetres
799
800 if (dWidth_ > dHeight_)
801 avg_data_scale_ = dHeight_ / default_paper_height_;
802 else
803 avg_data_scale_ = dHeight_ / default_paper_width_;
804
805 isLandscape = true;
806 if (dWidth_ < (dHeight_ + (title_block_height_ * avg_data_scale_)) || !default_limits_)
807 {
808 page_width_ = default_paper_height_; // centimetres
809 isLandscape = false;
810 }
811
812 pprj_->p._page_width = page_width_ + 2;
813
814 // Scale (for A3 page width)
815 if ((rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) > Degrees(PI) || // wider than 180 degrees?
816 (upperDeg_ - lowerDeg_) > Degrees(PI_135)) // taller than 135 degrees?
817 {
818 // Set the appropriate map projection
819 if(!pprj_->p._user_defined_projection)
820 {
821 if ((upperDeg_ - lowerDeg_) > Degrees(PI_135)) // taller than 135 degrees?
822 {
823 // Print the entire world on a flat sheet
824 pprj_->p._projection = world;
825
826 // Calculate ground width, which in this case is the circumference of the world
827 dDimension_ = TWO_PI * datum_.GetEllipsoid().GetSemiMajor(); // set distance circumference of a circle
828
829 // Centre world map according to data centre
830 leftDeg_ = centre_width_ - 180.0;
831 rightDeg_ = centre_width_ + 180.0;
832
833 // Normalise limits according to 180 boundary
834 if (leftDeg_ < -180.0)
835 leftDeg_ += 180.0;
836 if (rightDeg_ > 180.0)
837 rightDeg_ -= 180.0;
838
839 // Set latitude limits
840 lowerDeg_ = -90;
841 upperDeg_ = 90;
842 }
843 else
844 {
845 // Print a globe plot. Limits are not required
846 pprj_->p._projection = orthographic;
847
848 // Calculate ground width between west and east limits (including buffer)
849 dDimension_ = Radians(rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) / TWO_PI * datum_.GetEllipsoid().GetSemiMajor();
850 }
851 }
852 else
853 // Calculate ground width between west and east limits (including buffer)
854 dDimension_ = Radians(rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) / TWO_PI * datum_.GetEllipsoid().GetSemiMajor();
855
856 // Calculate scale
857 scale_ = dDimension_ / page_width_ * 100; // metres
858 }
859 else
860 {
861 double azimuth;
862
863 // Calculate accurate map width from limits
864 dDimension_ = RobbinsReverse<double>( // calculate distance (in metres) of map width
865 Radians(centre_height_), Radians(leftDeg_), Radians(centre_height_), Radians(rightDeg_),
866 &azimuth, datum_.GetEllipsoidRef());
867
868 // Calculate scale
869 scale_ = dDimension_ / page_width_ * 100; // metres
870
871 if (!pprj_->p._user_defined_projection)
872 {
873 // default (large regions)
874 pprj_->p._projection = mercator;
875
876 // very high latitudes
877 if (fabs(centre_height_) > 80.)
878 pprj_->p._projection = orthographic;
879 //
880 // high latitudes
881 else if (fabs(centre_height_) > 60.)
882 pprj_->p._projection = albersConic;
883 // sparse latitude coverage
884 else if ((upperDeg_ - lowerDeg_) > Degrees(QUART_PI)) // taller than 45 degrees?
885 {
886 // tall, narrow plots
887 if ((rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) < Degrees(QUART_PI)) // not more than 45 degrees wide?
888 pprj_->p._projection = orthographic;
889 // reasonably large area
890 else
891 pprj_->p._projection = mercator;
892 }
893 //
894 // Smallish areas
895 else if (scale_ < 750000 && scale_ > 5000)
896 pprj_->p._projection = transverseMercator;
897 //
898 // wider than 20 degrees and taller than 20 degrees?
899 else if ((rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) > Degrees(PI_20) && (upperDeg_ - lowerDeg_) > Degrees(PI_20))
900 pprj_->p._projection = stereographicConformal;
901 //
902 // wide plots
903 else if ((rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) > Degrees(THIRD_PI)) // wider than 90 degrees?
904
905 pprj_->p._projection = lambertEqualArea;
906 }
907 }
908
909 // Update calling app's parameters
910 pprj_->p._projection = pprj_->p._projection;
911 pprj_->p._ground_width = dDimension_;
912
913 // Normalise scale
914 NormaliseScale(scale_);
915 mapScale_ = scale_;
916
917 // Calculate scale bar, then round
918 scale_bar_width_ = dDimension_ / 3000.; // convert to kilometres
919 NormaliseScaleBar(scale_bar_width_);
920
921 // Calculate best graticule width, then round to the best integer
922 graticule_width_ = ((rightDeg_ - leftDeg_) / 4.);
923 graticule_width_precision_ = 12;
924 NormaliseGraticule(graticule_width_, graticule_width_precision_);
925
926 scale_precision_ = 0;
927 if (scale_bar_width_ < 1.0)
928 scale_precision_ = 4;
929
930 line_width_ = projectSettings_.p._msr_line_width;
931 circle_radius_ = 0.2;
932 circle_radius_2_ = circle_radius_;
933 circle_line_width_ = (projectSettings_.p._msr_line_width * 1.5);
934
935 //if (scale >= 900000)
936 //{
937 // //line_width = 0.05;
938 // circle_radius = 0.05;
939 // circle_line_width = 0.05;
940 //}
941
942 // Determine coastline resolution
943 coastResolution_ = "l";
944 SelectCoastlineResolution(dDimension_, coastResolution_, &pprj_->p);
945}

1050void dna_plot::InitialiseGMTFilenames()
1051{
1052 // create bat file name(s), one per block, as:
1053 // create_<network_name>_block_#.[bat|sh]
1054 //
1055 // Simultaneous plot cmd files are created as:
1056 // create_<network_name>_block_0.[bat|sh]
1057 //
1058 // Specific block (n) plot cmd files are created as:
1059 // create_<network_name>_block_n.[bat|sh]
1060 v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.clear();
1061 v_gmt_pdf_filenames_.clear();
1062 std::string gmt_filename, gmt_cmd_basename("create_" + network_name_ + "_block_");
1063
1064 UINT32 block;
1065 bool oneBlockOnly = InitialiseandValidateStartingBlock(block);
1066
1067 for (; block<blockCount_; ++block)
1068 {
1069 // gmt command filename
1070 gmt_filename = gmt_cmd_basename;
1071 gmt_filename.append(StringFromT(block)).append(_CMD_EXT_);
1072
1073 // Add folder path
1074 gmt_filename = pprj_->g.output_folder + FOLDER_SLASH + gmt_filename;
1075
1076 // Create absolute path
1077 gmt_filename = boost::filesystem::absolute(gmt_filename).string();
1078
1079 // Add to the list
1080 v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.push_back(gmt_filename);
1081
1082 // generated pdf filename
1083 gmt_filename = network_name_;
1084 gmt_filename.append("_block_").append(StringFromT(block)).append(".pdf");
1085 v_gmt_pdf_filenames_.push_back(output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + gmt_filename);
1086
1087 // break out for specific block (n) plots
1088 if (oneBlockOnly)
1089 break;
1090 }
1091
1092 pprj_->p._gmt_cmd_file = output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + leafStr(v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.at(0));
1093
1094 pprj_->p._pdf_file_name = output_folder_ + FOLDER_SLASH + network_name_;
1095
1096 if (plotBlocks_)
1097 pprj_->p._pdf_file_name.append("-phased");
1098 else
1099 pprj_->p._pdf_file_name.append("-simult");
1100
1101 if (plotBlocks_ && oneBlockOnly)
1102 pprj_->p._pdf_file_name.append("-block-").append(StringFromT(block));
1103
1104 pprj_->p._pdf_file_name.append(".pdf");
1105
1106 // simultaneous
1107 if (!plotBlocks_)
1108 v_gmt_pdf_filenames_.at(0) = pprj_->p._pdf_file_name;
1109}

1111void dna_plot::CreateGMTCommandFiles()
1112{
1113 UINT32 block(0);
1114 bool oneBlockOnly(true);
1115
1116 if (plotBlocks_)
1117 {
1118 // one and only block?
1119 if ((oneBlockOnly = InitialiseandValidateStartingBlock(block)))
1120 block = 0;
1121 }
1122
1123 for (; block<blockCount_; ++block)
1124 {
1125 try {
1126 // Create GMT batch file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
1127 file_opener(gmtbat_file_, v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.at(block));
1128 }
1129 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
1130 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
1131 }
1132
1133 // set header
1134 gmtbat_file_ << _CMD_HEADER_ << std::endl;
1135
1136 // GMT bat file is printed last to reflect the options and dimensions as determined
1137 // by PrintStationsDataFile and PrintMeasurementsDatFiles
1138 CreateGMTCommandFile(block);
1139
1140 // close the file
1141 gmtbat_file_.close();
1142
1143 // change file permission to executable
1144#if defined(__linux) || defined(sun) || defined(__unix__) || defined(__APPLE__)
1145 std::string system_file_cmd = _CHMOD_CMD_ + v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.at(block);
1146 std::system(system_file_cmd.c_str());
1147#endif
1148
1149 // break out for specific block (n) plots
1150 if (oneBlockOnly)
1151 break;
1152 }
1153}

1155
1156void dna_plot::CreateGMTCommandFile(const UINT32& block)
1157{
1158 it_pair_string _it_colour;
1159 string_string_pair this_msr;
1160
1161 float annot_font_size_primary(9), label_font_size(11.);
1162 double symbol_offset(1.0);
1163 double label_offset(1.5);
1164 double error_ellipse_scale(uncertainty_legend_length_/largest_uncertainty_);
1165 UINT32 uncertainty_legend_precision(4);
1166
1167 std::string psTempFile("tmp-");
1168 psTempFile.append(StringFromT(block)).append(".ps");
1169 std::string pdfTempFile("tmp-");
1170 pdfTempFile.append(StringFromT(block)).append(".pdf");
1171
1172 std::string legendTempFile("map-block");
1173 legendTempFile.append(StringFromT(block)).append(".legend");
1174
1175 // make temporary directory for gmt.conf gmt.history to prevent corruption of
1176 // gmt.conf and gmt.history during parallel processing
1177 gmtbat_file_ << std::endl << _COMMENT_PREFIX_ << "Create temporary folder for gmt.conf and gmt.history" << std::endl;
1178
1179#if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__WIN32__)
1180 // set, create and provide access to temporary folder for gmt.conf file
1181 gmtbat_file_ << _MAKEENV_CMD_ << _GMT_TMP_DIR_ << "=%TEMP%\\gmt.block-" << block << std::endl;
1182 gmtbat_file_ << _MAKEDIR_CMD_ << _ENV_GMT_TMP_DIR_ << std::endl;
1183 //gmtbat_file_ << "icacls " << _ENV_GMT_TMP_DIR_ << " /grant Everyone:(f)" << std::endl;
1184
1185#elif defined(__linux) || defined(sun) || defined(__unix__) || defined(__APPLE__)
1186 // temporary gmt.conf file location
1187 gmtbat_file_ << _MAKEENV_CMD_ << _GMT_TMP_DIR_ << "=$(" << _MAKETEMP_CMD_ << "-d ${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/gmt.XXXXXX)" << std::endl << std::endl;
1188#endif
1189
1190 UINT32 colours(0), columns(5);
1191
1192 if (plotBlocks_)
1193 gmtbat_file_ << std::endl <<
1194 _COMMENT_PREFIX_ << "GMT command file for segmented network block " << (block + 1) << std::endl;
1195 else
1196 gmtbat_file_ << std::endl <<
1197 _COMMENT_PREFIX_ << "GMT command file for simultaneous network" << std::endl << std::endl;
1198
1199 // write GMT parameters
1200 PrintGMTParameters();
1201
1202 if (isLandscape)
1203 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " PS_PAGE_ORIENTATION landscape" << std::endl << std::endl;
1204 else
1205 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " PS_PAGE_ORIENTATION portrait" << std::endl << std::endl;
1206
1207 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " FONT_ANNOT " << std::fixed << std::setprecision(1) << annot_font_size_primary << "p" << std::endl;
1208 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " FONT_ANNOT_PRIMARY " << std::fixed << std::setprecision(1) << annot_font_size_primary << "p" << std::endl;
1209 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " FONT_LABEL " << std::fixed << std::setprecision(1) << label_font_size << "p" << std::endl;
1210 if (graticule_width_ < 60./3600.)
1211 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " FORMAT_GEO_MAP ddd:mm:ss.x" << std::endl << std::endl;
1212 else
1213 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_GMTSET_ << " FORMAT_GEO_MAP ddd:mm" << std::endl << std::endl;
1214
1215 page_width_ = pprj_->p._page_width;
1216
1217 switch (pprj_->p._projection)
1218 {
1219 case world:
1220 // World map centered on the dateline
1221 // pscoast -Rg -JQ4.5i -B60f30g30 -Dc -A5000 -Gblack -P > tmp.ps
1222
1223 // Override coastline resolution
1224 coastResolution_ = "i";
1225 pprj_->p._coasline_resolution = intermediate;
1226 circle_radius_ = 0.02;
1227 circle_line_width_ = 0.02;
1228 if (pprj_->p._label_font_size < 0.)
1229 pprj_->p._label_font_size = 5;
1230
1231 gmtbat_file_ << _APP_PSCOAST_ << " -Rg" <<
1232 // Carree Cylindrical equidistant projection, which looks the nicest
1233 " -JQ" << page_width_ << "c -B60g30 -D" << coastResolution_ <<
1234 " -A10000 -W0.75p,16/169/243 -G245/245/245 -K > " << psTempFile << std::endl;
1235 //
1236 // Miller's Cylindrical projection, which is neither equal nor conformal. All meridians and parallels are straight lines.

2102 CreateGMTInputFiles();
2103
2104 FinaliseGMTParameters();
2105
2106 // for 1..n blocks, create a shell script that generates a PDF for
2107 // a single block. dnaplotwrapper can then execute each shell
2108 // script in parallel.
2109 CreateGMTCommandFiles();
2110
2111 // Now, based on font size determined by CreateGMTCommandFiles,
2112 // Print:
2113 // - stations labels,
2114 // - positional uncertainty,
2115 // - error ellipses, and
2116 // - correction arrows
2117 CreateExtraInputFiles();
2118}

2120void dna_plot::InvokeGMT()
2121{
2122 // set up a thread group to execute the GMT scripts in parallel
2123 boost::thread_group gmt_plot_threads;
2124
2125 for (UINT32 plot=0; plot<v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.size(); ++plot)
2126 {
2127 gmt_plot_threads.create_thread(dna_create_threaded_process(v_gmt_cmd_filenames_.at(plot)));
2128 }
2129
2130 // go!
2131 gmt_plot_threads.join_all();
2132}

2209{
2210 if (pprj_->p._bounding_box.empty())
2211 return;
2212
2213 if (GetFields(const_cast<char*>(pprj_->p._bounding_box.c_str()), ',', false, "ffff",
2214 &upperDeg_, &leftDeg_, &lowerDeg_, &rightDeg_ ) < 4)
2215 return;
2216
2217 upperDeg_ = DmstoDeg(upperDeg_);
2218 rightDeg_ = DmstoDeg(rightDeg_);
2219 lowerDeg_ = DmstoDeg(lowerDeg_);
2220 leftDeg_ = DmstoDeg(leftDeg_);
2221
2222 pprj_->p._plot_centre_longitude = (rightDeg_ + leftDeg_) / 2.0;
2223 pprj_->p._plot_centre_latitude = (upperDeg_ + lowerDeg_) / 2.0;
2224
2225 default_limits_ = false;

2421 _it_stn->stationConst[1] == 'C' ||

2600void dna_plot::PrintPositionalUncertainty(const UINT32& block)
2601{
2602 UINT32 block_index(block);
2603 if (plotBlocks_ && pprj_->p._plot_block_number > 0)
2604 block_index = 0;

2615 it_pair_string_vUINT32 _it_stnmap;

2617 UINT32 precision(10);

2620

2624 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(precision) << std::fixed << std::left << uncertainty_legend_lat_ << " " <<
2625 " 0 0 " <<
2626 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << std::right << largest_uncertainty_ << // semi-major
2627 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << std::right << largest_uncertainty_ << // semi-minor
2628 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(2) << std::fixed << std::right << "45.0" << std::endl; // orientation from e-axis

2631 _it_pu!=v_stn_pu_.end();

2643 bstBinaryRecords_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second).stationConst[1] == 'C')

2665void dna_plot::PrintErrorEllipses(const UINT32& block)
2666{
2667 UINT32 block_index(block);
2668 if (plotBlocks_ && pprj_->p._plot_block_number > 0)
2669 block_index = 0;
2670
2671 std::ofstream stn_err;
2672 try {
2673 // Create error ellipse file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
2674 file_opener(stn_err, v_stn_err_file_.at(block_index));
2675 }
2676 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
2677 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
2678 }
2679
2680 it_pair_string_vUINT32 _it_stnmap;
2681 it_vstn_t_const _it_stn(bstBinaryRecords_.begin());
2682 UINT32 precision(10);
2683
2684 it_vstnPU_t _it_pu;
2685
2686 double ellipse_scale(1.);
2687
2688 // The error ellipse legend is printed using the largest uncertainty (semi-major) found, unless
2689 // positional uncertainty is being printed, in which case the error ellipse is printed using
2690 // half the size. This is purely to give the impression that error ellipses are 1 sigma (68%) and
2691 // positional uncertainty is 95%, or close to 2 sigma.
2692 if (pprj_->p._plot_positional_uncertainty)
2693 ellipse_scale = 2.;
2694
2695 // Print uncertainty legend, using average xx length. See LoadPosUncertaintyFile().
2696 stn_err <<
2697 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(precision) << std::fixed << std::left << uncertainty_legend_long_ << " " <<
2698 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(precision) << std::fixed << std::left << uncertainty_legend_lat_ << " " <<
2699 " 0 0 " <<
2700 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << std::right <<
2701 largest_uncertainty_ / ellipse_scale << // semi-major
2702 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << std::right <<
2703 largest_uncertainty_ / 3.0 / ellipse_scale << // semi-minor
2704 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(2) << std::fixed << std::right <<
2705 "45.0" << std::endl; // orientation from e-axis
2706
2707 double angle;
2708
2709 for (_it_pu=v_stn_pu_.begin();
2710 _it_pu!=v_stn_pu_.end();
2711 ++_it_pu)
2712 {
2713 _it_stnmap = equal_range(stnsMap_.begin(), stnsMap_.end(), _it_pu->_station, StationNameIDCompareName());
2714
2715 // Not in the list? (Unlikely since adjust output will not contain stations not in the map, but test anyway)
2716 if (_it_stnmap.first == _it_stnmap.second)
2717 continue;
2718
2719 // no need to plot constrained stations - the uncertainties will be zero!!!
2720 // Horizontal only!!!
2721 if (bstBinaryRecords_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second).stationConst[0] == 'C' &&
2722 bstBinaryRecords_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second).stationConst[1] == 'C')
2723 continue;
2724
2725 if (plotBlocks_)
2726 // If this station is not in this block, don't print
2727 if (!binary_search(v_parameterStationList_.at(block).begin(), v_parameterStationList_.at(block).end(),
2728 _it_stnmap.first->second))
2729 continue;
2730
2731 // reduce error ellipse orientation in terms of
2732 // positive anti-clockwise direction from e-axis
2733 if (_it_pu->_orientation > 90.)
2734 angle = -(_it_pu->_orientation - 90.);
2735 else
2736 angle = DegtoDms(90. - DmstoDeg(_it_pu->_orientation));
2737
2738 stn_err <<
2739 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(precision) << std::fixed << std::left << _it_pu->_longitude << " " <<
2740 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(precision) << std::fixed << std::left << _it_pu->_latitude << " " <<
2741 " 0 0 " <<
2742 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << std::right << _it_pu->_semimMajor * pprj_->p._pu_ellipse_scale <<
2743 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::scientific << std::right << _it_pu->_semimMinor * pprj_->p._pu_ellipse_scale <<
2744 std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(4) << std::fixed << std::right << angle << std::endl;
2745 }
2746
2747 stn_err.close();
2748}

3437void dna_plot::LoadBinaryFiles()
3438{
3439 try {
3440 // Load binary stations data. Throws runtime_error on failure.
3441 dna_io_bst bst;
3442 stationCount_ = bst.load_bst_file(projectSettings_.i.bst_file, &bstBinaryRecords_, bst_meta_);
3443
3444 // Load binary stations data. Throws runtime_error on failure.
3445 dna_io_bms bms;
3446 bms.load_bms_file(projectSettings_.i.bms_file, &bmsBinaryRecords_, bms_meta_);
3447 }
3448 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
3449 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
3450 }
3451
3452 reference_frame_ = projectSettings_.i.reference_frame;
3453
3454 try {
3455 reference_frame_ = datumFromEpsgString<std::string>(bst_meta_.epsgCode);
3456 }
3457 catch (...) {
3458 // do nothing
3459 }
3460
3461 for_each(
3462 bstBinaryRecords_.begin(),
3463 bstBinaryRecords_.end(),
3464 [this] (station_t& stn) { // use lambda expression
3465 ReduceStationCoordinates(&stn);
3466 }
3467 );
3468
3469 // Create measurement tally to determine the measurement
3470 // types that have been supplied
3471 for_each(
3472 bmsBinaryRecords_.begin(),
3473 bmsBinaryRecords_.end(),
3474 [this] (measurement_t& msr) { // use lambda expression
3475
3476 switch (msr.measType)
3477 {
3478 case 'A': // Horizontal angle
3479 parsemsrTally_.A++;
3480 break;
3481 case 'B': // Geodetic azimuth
3482 parsemsrTally_.B++;
3483 break;
3484 case 'C': // Chord dist
3485 parsemsrTally_.C++;
3486 break;
3487 case 'D': // Direction set
3488 if (msr.vectorCount1 > 0)
3489 parsemsrTally_.D += msr.vectorCount1 - 1;
3490 break;
3491 case 'E': // Ellipsoid arc
3492 parsemsrTally_.E++;
3493 break;
3494 case 'G': // GPS Baseline
3495 parsemsrTally_.G++;
3496 break;
3497 case 'H': // Orthometric height
3498 parsemsrTally_.H++;
3499 break;
3500 case 'I': // Astronomic latitude
3501 parsemsrTally_.I++;
3502 break;
3503 case 'J': // Astronomic longitude
3504 parsemsrTally_.J++;
3505 break;
3506 case 'K': // Astronomic azimuth
3507 parsemsrTally_.K++;
3508 break;
3509 case 'L': // Level difference
3510 parsemsrTally_.L++;
3511 break;
3512 case 'M': // MSL arc
3513 parsemsrTally_.M++;
3514 break;
3515 case 'P': // Geodetic latitude
3516 parsemsrTally_.P++;
3517 break;
3518 case 'Q': // Geodetic longitude
3519 parsemsrTally_.Q++;
3520 break;
3521 case 'R': // Ellipsoidal height
3522 parsemsrTally_.R++;
3523 break;
3524 case 'S': // Slope distance
3525 parsemsrTally_.S++;
3526 break;
3527 case 'V': // Zenith distance
3528 parsemsrTally_.V++;
3529 break;
3530 case 'X': // GPS Baseline cluster
3531 if (msr.measStart == xMeas)
3532 {
3533 if (msr.vectorCount1 == msr.vectorCount2 + 1)
3534 parsemsrTally_.X += (msr.vectorCount1 * 3);
3535 }
3536 break;
3537 case 'Y': // GPS point cluster
3538 if (msr.measStart == xMeas)
3539 {
3540 if (msr.vectorCount1 == msr.vectorCount2 + 1)
3541 parsemsrTally_.Y += (msr.vectorCount1 * 3);
3542 }
3543 break;
3544 case 'Z': // Vertical angle
3545 parsemsrTally_.Z++;
3546 break;
3547 }
3548 }
3549 );
3550
3551 measurementCount_ = parsemsrTally_.TotalCount();
3552
3553}

3624void dna_plot::LoadPosUncertaintyFile()
3625{
3626 // Load corrections file generated by adjust
3627 std::ifstream apu_file;
3628 try {
3629 // Load apu file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
3630 file_opener(apu_file, projectSettings_.o._apu_file, std::ios::in, ascii, true);
3631 }
3632 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
3633 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
3634 }
3635
3636 bool fullCovarianceMatrix(false);
3637 UINT32 block(0), stn(0), stn_cov, blockstnCount;
3638 std::string strLine;
3639 stationPosUncertainty_t posUnc;
3640
3641 v_stn_pu_.resize(blockCount_);
3642 largest_uncertainty_ = 0.0;
3643
3644 char line[PRINT_LINE_LENGTH];
3645 bool dataBlocks(false);
3646 it_pair_string_vUINT32 _it_stnmap;
3647
3648 APU_UNITS_UI vcv_units;
3649 matrix_2d vcv_cart(3, 3), vcv_local(3, 3);
3650
3651 try {
3652
3653 // read header line
3654 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3655 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // DYNADJUST POSITIONAL UNCERTAINTY...
3656 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
3657 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Version
3658 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Build
3659 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // File created
3660 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // File name
3661 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
3662 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // PU Confidence interval
3663 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Error ellipse axes
3664 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Variances
3665
3666 apu_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Stations printed in blocks
3667 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
3668 if (!boost::iequals(strLine.substr(0, 16), "Stations printed"))
3669 {
3670 std::stringstream ss;
3671 ss << "LoadPosUncertaintyFile(): " << projectSettings_.o._apu_file << " is corrupt." << std::endl;
3672 ss << " Expected to find 'Stations printed in blocks' field." << std::endl;
3673 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &apu_file);
3674 }
3675
3676 if ((dataBlocks = yesno_uint<bool, std::string>(strLine.substr(PRINT_VAR_PAD))))
3677 v_stn_pu_.resize(bstBinaryRecords_.size());
3678 else
3679 v_stn_pu_.reserve(bstBinaryRecords_.size());
3680
3681 apu_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Variance matrix units
3682 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
3683 if (boost::iequals(strLine.substr(PRINT_VAR_PAD, 3), "XYZ"))
3684 vcv_units = XYZ_apu_ui;
3685 else
3686 vcv_units = ENU_apu_ui;
3687
3688
3689 apu_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Full covariance matrix
3690 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
3691 if (!boost::iequals(strLine.substr(0, 15), "Full covariance"))
3692 {
3693 std::stringstream ss;
3694 ss << "LoadPosUncertaintyFile(): " << projectSettings_.o._apu_file << " is corrupt." << std::endl;
3695 ss << " Expected to find 'Full covariance matrix' field." << std::endl;
3696 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &apu_file);
3697 }
3698
3699 fullCovarianceMatrix = yesno_uint<bool, std::string>(strLine.substr(PRINT_VAR_PAD));
3700
3701 // If covariances are printed, then the data will appear in blocks
3702 if (fullCovarianceMatrix)
3703 dataBlocks = true;
3704
3705 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3706 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
3707 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Positional uncertainty of ...
3708 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3709
3710 for (block=0; block<blockCount_; ++block)
3711 {
3712 if (dataBlocks)
3713 {
3714 blockstnCount = static_cast<UINT32>(v_ISL_.at(block).size() + v_JSL_.at(block).size());
3715

3725 ss << " Expected to read Block data, but found " << strLine << std::endl;
3726 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &apu_file);
3727 }
3728
3729 if (LongFromString<UINT32>(strLine.substr(6)) != block + 1)
3730 {
3731 std::stringstream ss;
3732 ss << "LoadPosUncertaintyFile(): " << projectSettings_.o._apu_file << " is corrupt." << std::endl;
3733 ss << " Expected to read data for block " << strLine.substr(6) << ", but found " << strLine << std::endl;
3734 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &apu_file);
3735 }
3736 }
3737 else
3738 {
3739 blockstnCount = stationCount_;
3740 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
3741 }
3742
3743 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Station
3744 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3745
3746 for (stn=0; stn<blockstnCount; ++stn)
3747 {
3748 apu_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Now the data...
3749

3751 if (strLine.length() < STATION)
3752 {

3754 break;

3760 posUnc._longitude = DmstoDeg(DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST, LON_NORTH))));
3761 posUnc._hzPosU = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH, STAT)));
3762 posUnc._vtPosU = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT, STAT)));
3763 posUnc._semimMajor = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT, PREC)));
3764 posUnc._semimMinor = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT+PREC, PREC)));
3765 posUnc._orientation = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT+PREC+PREC, PREC)));
3766 posUnc._xx = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT+PREC+PREC+PREC, MSR)));
3767 posUnc._xy = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT+PREC+PREC+PREC+MSR, MSR)));

3769

3771 apu_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH);
3772 strLine = std::string(line);
3773 posUnc._yy = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT+PREC+PREC+PREC+MSR, MSR)));
3774 posUnc._yz = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+LAT_EAST+LON_NORTH+STAT+STAT+PREC+PREC+PREC+MSR+MSR, MSR)));
3775
3776 // Get reference of this station in bstBinaryRecords.
3777 if (dataBlocks || vcv_units == XYZ_apu_ui)
3778 {
3779 _it_stnmap = equal_range(stnsMap_.begin(), stnsMap_.end(), posUnc._station, StationNameIDCompareName());
3780
3781 // Not in the list? (Unlikely since adjust output will not contain stations not in the map, but test anyway)
3782 if (_it_stnmap.first == _it_stnmap.second)
3783 continue;
3784 }
3785
3786 // Calculate vcv in local reference frame
3787 if (vcv_units == XYZ_apu_ui)
3788 {
3789 // get yy from next row of variance matrix
3790 apu_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH);
3791 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
3792 posUnc._zz = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine));
3793
3794 vcv_cart.put(0, 0, posUnc._xx);
3795 vcv_cart.put(0, 1, posUnc._xy);
3796 vcv_cart.put(0, 2, posUnc._xz);
3797 vcv_cart.put(1, 1, posUnc._yy);
3798 vcv_cart.put(1, 2, posUnc._yz);
3799 vcv_cart.put(2, 2, posUnc._zz);
3800
3801 vcv_cart.filllower();
3802
3803 // Calculate correlations in local reference frame
3804 PropagateVariances_LocalCart<double>(vcv_cart, vcv_local,
3805 bstBinaryRecords_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second).currentLatitude,
3806 bstBinaryRecords_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second).currentLongitude, false);
3807
3808 posUnc._xx = vcv_local.get(0, 0);
3809 posUnc._xy = vcv_local.get(0, 1);
3810 posUnc._xz = vcv_local.get(0, 2);
3811 posUnc._yy = vcv_local.get(1, 1);
3812 posUnc._yz = vcv_local.get(1, 2);
3813 posUnc._zz = vcv_local.get(2, 2);
3814 }
3815 else
3816 // ENU - don't need up component - ignore last (height) row
3817 // of variance matrix
3818 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3819
3820 // Data in blocks? Set the vector element accordingly, otherwise add to the vector
3821 if (dataBlocks)
3822 v_stn_pu_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second) = posUnc;
3823 else
3824 v_stn_pu_.push_back(posUnc);
3825
3826 if (fabs(posUnc._semimMajor) > largest_uncertainty_)
3827 largest_uncertainty_ = posUnc._semimMajor;
3828
3829 if (!fullCovarianceMatrix)
3830 continue;
3831
3832 // skip over covariances
3833 for (stn_cov=stn+1; stn_cov<blockstnCount; ++stn_cov)
3834 {
3835 // ignore covariance block
3836 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3837 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3838 apu_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
3839 }
3840 }
3841 }
3842 }
3843 catch (const std::ios_base::failure& f) {
3844 if (!apu_file.eof())
3845 {
3846 std::stringstream ss;
3847 ss << "LoadPosUncertaintyFile(): An error was encountered when reading " << projectSettings_.o._apu_file << "." << std::endl << " " << f.what();
3848 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &apu_file);
3849 }
3850 }
3851
3852 apu_file.close();
3853}
3854
3855void dna_plot::ComputeStationCorrection(it_vstn_t_const _it_stn, stationCorrections_t& stnCor,
3856 matrix_2d& currentEstimates, matrix_2d& initialEstimates)
3857{
3858 // Compute XYZ for current estimates
3859 GeoToCart<double>(
3860 _it_stn->currentLatitude,
3861 _it_stn->currentLongitude,
3862 _it_stn->currentHeight,
3863 currentEstimates.getelementref(0, 0),
3864 currentEstimates.getelementref(1, 0),
3865 currentEstimates.getelementref(2, 0),
3866 datum_.GetEllipsoidRef());
3867
3868 // Compute XYZ for initial estimates
3869 GeoToCart<double>(
3870 Radians(_it_stn->initialLatitude),
3871 Radians(_it_stn->initialLongitude),
3872 _it_stn->initialHeight + _it_stn->geoidSep,
3873 initialEstimates.getelementref(0, 0),
3874 initialEstimates.getelementref(1, 0),
3875 initialEstimates.getelementref(2, 0),
3876 datum_.GetEllipsoidRef());
3877
3878 // compute vertical angle
3879 stnCor._vAngle = VerticalAngle<double>(
3880 initialEstimates.get(0, 0), // X1
3881 initialEstimates.get(1, 0), // Y1
3882 initialEstimates.get(2, 0), // Z1
3883 currentEstimates.get(0, 0), // X2
3884 currentEstimates.get(1, 0), // Y2
3885 currentEstimates.get(2, 0), // Z2
3886 _it_stn->currentLatitude,
3887 _it_stn->currentLongitude,
3888 _it_stn->currentLatitude,
3889 _it_stn->currentLongitude,
3890 0., 0.,
3891 &stnCor._east, &stnCor._north, &stnCor._up);
3892
3893 if (fabs(stnCor._east) < PRECISION_1E5)
3894 if (fabs(stnCor._north) < PRECISION_1E5)
3895 if (fabs(stnCor._up) < PRECISION_1E5)
3896 stnCor._vAngle = 0.;
3897
3898 // compute horizontal correction
3899 stnCor._hDistance = magnitude(stnCor._east, stnCor._north);
3900
3901 // calculate azimuth
3902 stnCor._azimuth = Direction<double>(
3903 initialEstimates.get(0, 0), // X1
3904 initialEstimates.get(1, 0), // Y1
3905 initialEstimates.get(2, 0), // Z1
3906 currentEstimates.get(0, 0), // X2
3907 currentEstimates.get(1, 0), // Y2
3908 currentEstimates.get(2, 0), // Z2
3909 _it_stn->currentLatitude,
3910 _it_stn->currentLongitude,
3911 &stnCor._east, &stnCor._north);
3912
3913 if (fabs(stnCor._east) < PRECISION_1E5)
3914 if (fabs(stnCor._north) < PRECISION_1E5)
3915 stnCor._azimuth = 0.;
3916
3917 // calculate distances
3918 stnCor._sDistance = magnitude<double>(
3919 initialEstimates.get(0, 0), // X1
3920 initialEstimates.get(1, 0), // Y1
3921 initialEstimates.get(2, 0), // Z1
3922 currentEstimates.get(0, 0), // X2
3923 currentEstimates.get(1, 0), // Y2
3924 currentEstimates.get(2, 0)); // Z2
3925}
3926
3927
3928void dna_plot::ComputeStationCorrections()
3929{
3930 // reserve enough memory for each station
3931 v_stn_corrs_.reserve(bstBinaryRecords_.size());
3932
3933 stationCorrections_t stnCor;
3934 matrix_2d currentEstimates(3, 1), initialEstimates(3, 1);
3935
3936 average_correction_ = 0.0;
3937 UINT32 correction_count(0);
3938
3939 // compute corrections for every station in the network
3940 for (it_vstn_t_const _it_stn=bstBinaryRecords_.begin();
3941 _it_stn!=bstBinaryRecords_.end();
3942 ++_it_stn)
3943 {
3944 // Constrained? No correction!
3945 if (_it_stn->stationConst[0] == 'C' &&
3946 _it_stn->stationConst[1] == 'C' &&
3947 _it_stn->stationConst[2] == 'C')
3948 {
3949 // push a zero correction
3950 v_stn_corrs_.push_back(stationCorrections(_it_stn->stationName));
3951 continue;
3952 }
3953
3954 stnCor._station = _it_stn->stationName;
3955 ComputeStationCorrection(_it_stn, stnCor,
3956 currentEstimates, initialEstimates);
3957
3958 average_correction_ += stnCor._hDistance;
3959 correction_count++;
3960
3961 v_stn_corrs_.push_back(stnCor);
3962 }
3963
3964 // determine average correction length
3965 average_correction_ /= correction_count;
3966}

3968void dna_plot::BuildParameterStationList()
3969{
3970 if (!plotBlocks_)
3971 return;
3972
3973 v_parameterStationList_.resize(blockCount_);
3974
3975 vUINT32 vStns;
3976 it_vUINT32_const _it_stn;
3977
3978 for (UINT32 block(0); block!=blockCount_; ++block)
3979 {
3980 // Form combined stations list
3981 v_parameterStationList_.at(block) = v_ISL_.at(block);
3982 v_parameterStationList_.at(block).insert(v_parameterStationList_.at(block).end(),
3983 v_JSL_.at(block).begin(), v_JSL_.at(block).end());
3984 std::sort(v_parameterStationList_.at(block).begin(), v_parameterStationList_.at(block).end());
3985
3986 }
3987}
3988
3989// The station corrections file is produced by adjust. Note that corrections for *all* stations may not
3990// be printed, since the user has the option to restrict the output of station corrections using
3991// horizontal and vertical thresholds.
3992// Also, the coorctions file may contain a list of stations printed in blocks, or in a contiguous list.
3993// These options create complexities!
3994//
3995// The best way to deal with station corrections is to ignore the cor file and to recalculate corrections
3996// from the original coordinates in the bst file.
3997void dna_plot::LoadCorrectionsFile()
3998{
3999 // Load corrections file generated by adjust
4000 std::ifstream cor_file;
4001 try {
4002 // Load corrections file. Throws runtime_error on failure.
4003 file_opener(cor_file, projectSettings_.o._cor_file, std::ios::in, ascii, true);
4004 }
4005 catch (const std::runtime_error& e) {
4006 SignalExceptionPlot(e.what(), 0, NULL);
4007 }
4008
4009 UINT32 correction_count(0);
4010 UINT32 block(0), stn(0), blockstnCount, corFileBlockCount(blockCount_);
4011 std::string strLine;
4012 stationCorrections_t stnCor;
4013
4014 average_correction_ = 0.0;
4015
4016 char line[PRINT_LINE_LENGTH];
4017 bool dataBlocks(false);
4018 it_pair_string_vUINT32 _it_stnmap;
4019
4020 try {
4021
4022 // read header line
4023 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
4024 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // DYNADJUST CORRECT...
4025 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
4026 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Version
4027 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Build
4028 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // File created
4029 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // File name
4030 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
4031 cor_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Stations printed in blocks
4032
4033 // Get the yes/no string and convert to bool
4034 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
4035 if (!boost::iequals(strLine.substr(0, 16), "Stations printed"))
4036 {
4037 std::stringstream ss;
4038 // TODO - make use of Boost current function
4039 // http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_58_0/boost/current_function.hpp
4040 // and if required, print the filename and line number using __FILE__ and __LINE__
4041 // https://stackoverflow.com/questions/15305310/predefined-macros-for-function-name-func
4042 ss << "LoadCorrectionsFile(): " << projectSettings_.o._cor_file << " is corrupt." << std::endl;
4043 ss << " Expected to find 'Stations printed in blocks' field." << std::endl;
4044 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &cor_file);
4045 }
4046
4047 if ((dataBlocks = yesno_uint<bool, std::string>(strLine.substr(PRINT_VAR_PAD)))) // Data printed in blocks?
4048 v_stn_corrs_.resize(bstBinaryRecords_.size());
4049 else
4050 {
4051 v_stn_corrs_.reserve(bstBinaryRecords_.size());
4052 corFileBlockCount = 1;
4053 }
4054
4055 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
4056 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Corrections to Stations
4057 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
4058
4059 for (block=0; block<corFileBlockCount; ++block)
4060 {
4061 if (dataBlocks)
4062 {
4063 blockstnCount = static_cast<UINT32>(v_ISL_.at(block).size() + v_JSL_.at(block).size());
4064
4065 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
4066 cor_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Block #
4067
4068 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
4069
4070 if (!boost::iequals(strLine.substr(0, 5), "Block"))
4071 {
4072 std::stringstream ss;
4073 ss << "LoadCorrectionsFile(): " << projectSettings_.o._cor_file << " is corrupt." << std::endl;
4074 ss << " Expected to read Block data, but found " << strLine << std::endl;
4075 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &cor_file);
4076 }
4077
4078 if (LongFromString<UINT32>(strLine.substr(6)) != block + 1)
4079 {
4080 std::stringstream ss;
4081 ss << "LoadCorrectionsFile(): " << projectSettings_.o._cor_file << " is corrupt." << std::endl;
4082 ss << " Expected to read data for block " << strLine.substr(6) << ", but found " << strLine << std::endl;
4083 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &cor_file);
4084 }
4085 }
4086 else
4087 {
4088 blockstnCount = stationCount_;
4089 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); //
4090 }
4091
4092 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // Station
4093 cor_file.ignore(PRINT_LINE_LENGTH, '\n'); // ------------------------
4094
4095 for (stn=0; stn<blockstnCount; ++stn)
4096 {
4097 cor_file.getline(line, PRINT_LINE_LENGTH); // Now the data...
4098
4099 strLine = trimstr(std::string(line));
4100 if (strLine.length() < STATION)
4101 {
4102 if (cor_file.eof())
4103 break;
4104 continue;
4105 }
4106
4109 //os << std::setw(STATION) << std::left << bstBinaryRecords_.at(stn).stationName << std::setw(PAD2) << " ";
4111 //os << std::setw(MSR) << std::right << FormatDmsString(RadtoDms(azimuth), 4, true, false) <<
4112 // std::setw(MSR) << std::right << FormatDmsString(RadtoDms(vertical_angle), 4, true, false) <<
4113 // std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(PRECISION_MTR_STN) << std::fixed << std::right << slope_distance <<
4114 // std::setw(MSR) << std::setprecision(PRECISION_MTR_STN) << std::fixed << std::right << horiz_distance <<
4115 // std::setw(HEIGHT) << std::setprecision(PRECISION_MTR_STN) << std::fixed << std::right << local_12e <<
4116 // std::setw(HEIGHT) << std::setprecision(PRECISION_MTR_STN) << std::fixed << std::right << local_12n <<
4117 // std::setw(HEIGHT) << std::setprecision(PRECISION_MTR_STN) << std::fixed << std::right << local_12up << std::endl;
4118
4119 stnCor._station = trimstr(strLine.substr(0, STATION));
4120 stnCor._azimuth = ParseDmsString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2, MSR)), " ");
4121 stnCor._vAngle = ParseDmsString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+MSR, MSR)), " ");
4122 stnCor._sDistance = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+MSR+MSR, MSR)));
4123 stnCor._hDistance = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+MSR+MSR+MSR, MSR)));
4124 stnCor._east = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+MSR+MSR+MSR+MSR, HEIGHT)));
4125 stnCor._north = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+MSR+MSR+MSR+MSR+HEIGHT, HEIGHT)));
4126 stnCor._up = DoubleFromString<double>(trimstr(strLine.substr(STATION+PAD2+MSR+MSR+MSR+MSR+HEIGHT+HEIGHT, HEIGHT)));
4127
4128
4129 // Get reference of this station in bstBinaryRecords.
4130 if (dataBlocks)
4131 {
4132 _it_stnmap = equal_range(stnsMap_.begin(), stnsMap_.end(), stnCor._station, StationNameIDCompareName());
4133
4134 // Not in the list? (Unlikely since adjust output will not contain stations not in the map, but test anyway)
4135 if (_it_stnmap.first == _it_stnmap.second)
4136 continue;
4137
4138 v_stn_corrs_.at(_it_stnmap.first->second) = stnCor;
4139 }
4140 else
4141 v_stn_corrs_.push_back(stnCor);
4142
4143 average_correction_ += stnCor._hDistance;
4144 correction_count++;
4145 }
4146 }
4147 }
4148 catch (const std::ios_base::failure& f) {
4149 if (!cor_file.eof())
4150 {
4151 std::stringstream ss;
4152 ss << "LoadCorrectionsFile(): An error was encountered when reading " << projectSettings_.o._cor_file << "." << std::endl << " " << f.what();
4153 SignalExceptionPlot(ss.str(), 0, "i", &cor_file);
4154 }
4155 }
4156
4157 // determine average correction length
4158 average_correction_ /= correction_count;
4159
4160 cor_file.close();
4161}

4164// Name: SignalExceptionPlot
4165// Purpose: Closes all files (if file pointers are passed in) and throws runtime_error
4166// Called by: Any
4167// Calls: runtime_error()
4168void dna_plot::SignalExceptionPlot(const std::string& msg, const int& line_no, const char *streamType, ...)
4169{
4170 plotStatus_ = PLOT_EXCEPTION_RAISED;
4171
4172 if (streamType == NULL)
4173 throw NetPlotException(msg, line_no);
4174
4175 std::ofstream* ofsDynaML;
4176 std::ifstream* ifsbinaryFile;
4177
4178 va_list argptr;
4179 va_start(argptr, streamType);
4180
4181 while (*streamType != '\0')
4182 {
4183 //ifstream
4184 if (*streamType == 'i' )
4185 {
4186 ifsbinaryFile = va_arg(argptr, std::ifstream*);
4187 ifsbinaryFile->close();
4188 }
4189 //ofstream
4190 if (*streamType == 'o' )
4191 {
4192 ofsDynaML = va_arg(argptr, std::ofstream*);
4193 ofsDynaML->close();
4194 }
4195 streamType++;
4196 }
4197
4198 va_end(argptr);
4199
4200 throw NetPlotException(msg, line_no);
4201}

4523 else if (graticule > 3600) // 1 degrees

4535 else if (graticule > 30) // 30 seconds

4537 else if (graticule > 15) // 15 seconds

4539 else if (graticule > 10) // 10 seconds
